All 3 violations fixed and committed. Here's what changed:

**Pattern applied to all 3 pages:** Lifted `<PageHeader>` (which renders the `<h1>`) from client components up to their server `page.tsx` files.

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `operations/page.tsx` | Added `<PageHeader title subtitle>` wrapping the client |
| `operations-page-client.tsx` | Removed `PageHeader` import + usage |
| `students/page.tsx` | Added `<PageHeader title subtitle>` wrapping the client |
| `students-page-client.tsx` | Removed `PageHeader` from both branches; components now return bare `<EmptyState>` or `<DataTableShell>` |
| `overview/page.tsx` | Added `<PageHeader title subtitle actions={Button+Link}>` wrapping the client |
| `overview-page-client.tsx` | Removed `PageHeader`, `Button`, `Link` imports + the header block |

`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
This is a common Next.js a11y pitfall: static analysis scans server component files but can't cross the `'use client'` boundary into client components. The fix also improves architecture — static content like page titles belongs in server components (faster first paint, better SEO), while client components focus on interactive state.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
